<br>
The setup was simple:<br>
<br>
Using my focus items, I resummoned until I got a pet blue to him(except one case), armed it and buffed it with BO2.  He summoned his, buffed it with whatever pet buffs he had and he refused my offer to arm it(wanted it to be completely self buffed).<br>
<br>
Fire vs Skel<br>
------------<br>
Fire hit for 36 max<br>
Skel hit for 39 max<br>
<br>
Fire pet won with 46% health left<br>
<br>
Air vs Skel<br>
-----------<br>
Air hit for 38 max<br>
Skel hit for 33 max<br>
<br>
Air pet won with 32% health left<br>
(The funny thing about this one was my necro friend was confused by how much trouble his pet was having hitting mine.  You can see that by the max hit the skeleton had.  Nice ac air pet! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Water vs Skel<br>
-------------<br>
Water hit for 36<br>
Skel hit for 39<br>
<br>
Skeleton won with 17% health left<br>
<br>
Earth vs Skel<br>
-------------<br>
(We had two battles here..the first with a green one and one with blue.  Had the green battle because I tried resummoning 10 times all getting greens)<br>
<br>
Green Earth hit for 32 max<br>
Skel hit for 39<br>
<br>
Skeleton won with 39% health left<br>
<br>
2nd battle<br>
(blue earth)<br>
-----------<br>
Blue earth hit for 36 max<br>
Skel hit fo 39<br>
<br>
Earth won with 22% health left<br>
<br>
---------------------------------------------<br>
There's a big difference between the green and blue pet isn't there?  However, I was actually expecting the water pet(Always felt water was pretty strong) to win and the earth to lose.<br>
<br>
It seems that necros summon their pets near if not at their max every time.  Also, the necro hits appear to hit for more than our pets do on average.  (Yes, I know the max pet can hit for 40 but how often do you get that one?).<br>
